officials worked around centralized failings to build a more humane city. And hardly disengaged, residents turned to black-market construction to patch up their surroundings.Because such "urban ingenuity" was premised on weakness in the centralized regime, the dystopian cityscape evolved from being merely a "idian grievance to the backdrop for revolution. If, by their actions, officials were demonstrating that the regime was irrelevant, and if, in their own experiences, locals only attained basic repairs outside official channels, why should anyone have mourned the system when it was overthrown?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArchitecture and statezGermany (East). 0aCity planningxPolitical aspectszGermanyzLeipzigxHistoryy20th century. 0aCommunism and architecturezGermanyzLeipzig. 0aUrban renewalxPolitical aspectszGermanyzLeipzig. 0aUrban renewalzGermanyzLeipzigxCitizen participation. 0aUrban renewalzGermanyzLeipzigxHistoryy20th century. 4aHistory. 4aUrban Studies. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / Communism, Post-Communism & Socialism.2bisacsh  aEast Germany, 1989 Revolution, urban planning, civic initiative, late Communism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069046008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501751684?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501751684423Cove